2. Retrieving the images and their labels (Training Data)¶

In [4]:
imgs_path = "../input/gtsrb-german-traffic-sign/Train"
data_list = []
labels_list = []
classes_list = 43
for i in range(classes_list):
    i_path = os.path.join(imgs_path, str(i)) #0-42
    for img in os.listdir(i_path):
        im = Image.open(i_path +'/'+ img)
        im = im.resize((32,32))
        im = np.array(im)
        data_list.append(im)
        labels_list.append(i)
#Converting lists into numpy arrays
data = np.array(data_list)
labels = np.array(labels_list)

5. Model Building - Custom Model with Hyperparameters¶

In [16]:
from keras.layers import BatchNormalization
def own_model(hp):
    model = Sequential() #Sequential Instance

    #ConvLayer1 + MaxPooling + BatchNormalization + Dropout
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=hp.Int("conv_1_filter",min_value = 32,max_value = 128,step = 16),kernel_size=hp.Choice("conv_1_kernel", values = [3,5])
                     ,activation='relu',padding='same',input_shape=X_train.shape[1:]))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(strides=2))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.3))

    #ConvLayer2 + MaxPooling + BatchNormalization + Dropout
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=hp.Int("conv_2_filter",min_value = 48,max_value = 144,step = 16),kernel_size=hp.Choice("conv_2_kernel", values = [3,5])
                     ,activation='relu',padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(strides=2))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.3))

    #ConvLayer3 + Dropout + ConvLayer(512 filters) + MaxPooling + BatchNormalization
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=hp.Int("conv_3_filter",min_value = 352,max_value = 528,step = 16),kernel_size=hp.Choice("conv_3_kernel", values = [3,5])
                     ,activation='relu',padding='same'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.3))
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=512,kernel_size=3,activation='relu',padding='same'))
    model.add(MaxPool2D(strides=2))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())

    #Flatten
    model.add(Flatten())

    #2 Dense layers with hidden units
    model.add(Dense(units=hp.Int('dense_1_units', min_value=3800, max_value=4300, step=100),activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(units=hp.Int('dense_2_units', min_value=3800, max_value=4300, step=100),activation='relu'))
    #Dense layer with hidden units
    model.add(Dense(units=hp.Int('dense_3_units', min_value=800, max_value=1300, step=100),activation='relu'))
    #Softmax layer for output
    model.add(Dense(43,activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(optimizer= "adam",
                 loss='categorical_crossentropy',
                 metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

7 Transfer Learning Approach with Model Evaluation¶

In [44]:
def trans_learning(model):
    mod_name = model(input_shape=X_train.shape[1:],weights="imagenet",include_top=False)
    for layers in mod_name.layers:
        layers.trainable = False

    x = Flatten()(mod_name.output)
    op_layer = Dense(43,activation="softmax")(x)
    
    tl_model = Model(inputs = mod_name.input,outputs=op_layer)
    
    tl_model.compile(optimizer="adam",
             loss='categorical_crossentropy',
             metrics=["accuracy"])

    history2= tl_model.fit(aug.flow(X_train,y_train),
                 epochs=50,
                 batch_size=64,
                 validation_data=(X_val,y_val))
    
    
    #Plotting Graphs
    #Accuracy plot
    plt.figure(0)
    plt.plot(history2.history['accuracy'],label='training accuracy')
    plt.plot(history2.history['val_accuracy'],label='validation accuracy')
    plt.title('Accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('epochs')
    plt.ylabel('accuracy')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    
    #Loss plot
    plt.plot(history2.history['loss'],label='training loss')
    plt.plot(history2.history['val_loss'],label='validation loss')
    plt.title('Loss')
    plt.xlabel('epochs')
    plt.ylabel('loss')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    
    predict_tl_model=tl_model.predict(X_test) 
    pred_tl_model=np.argmax(predict_tl_model,axis=1)
    print(accuracy_score(test_labels, pred_tl_model))
    
    print(confusion_matrix(test_labels, pred_tl_model))
    
    print(classification_report(test_labels, pred_tl_model))
